# Deployment

## Required environment variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | Translation / analysis |
| `SUPABASE_URL` | Database, auth, storage |
| `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` | Client + user-scoped API |
| `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` | Server-side admin DB ops |
| `PORT` | API port (default 3000) |

See `@env.example.txt` for optional: chunking, `PUBLIC_URL`, `VITE_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID`, `VITE_SUPPORT_BOOSTY_URL`.

## Log shipping (Axiom, production)

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `LOG_SHIPPING` | `1` or `true` — enable async push to Axiom (production only in code) |
| `AXIOM_TOKEN` | Axiom ingest API token |
| `AXIOM_DATASET` | Dataset name (`arcane-prod` or `arcane-staging`) |
| `AXIOM_REGION` | `eu` — shorthand when datasets are in EU (sets `api.eu.axiom.co` + EU edge) |
| `AXIOM_URL` | Optional API base URL override (e.g. `https://api.eu.axiom.co`) |
| `AXIOM_EDGE` | Optional ingest edge domain (e.g. `eu-central-1.aws.edge.axiom.co`) |
| `LOG_LEVEL` | `info` recommended in prod |
| `ARCANE_ENV` | Optional deploy env label when not on Vercel |

Set on **Vercel** (Production + Preview) and **worker host**. Do not enable locally unless explicitly testing shipping. See `@docs/02-how-to/observability-axiom.md`.

## Async jobs (production)

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `REDIS_URL` | BullMQ connection (analysis/translate queues) |
| `KV_REST_API_URL` / `KV_REST_API_TOKEN` | Job state + cancel flags (worker) |

Without Redis: sync translate/analyze still work; async batch endpoints return **503** per `@.cursor/rules/routing.mdc`.

Web scraper is **not** part of arcane-reader deployment. See [arcane-scraper](https://github.com/arcane-scraper) (standalone dev tool).

## Local development

```bash
npm install
cp env.example.txt .env
npm run dev          # API + Vite client
npm run dev:full     # + BullMQ worker
```

## Build and run

```bash
npm run build        # client (Vite) + server (tsc)
npm run start        # node dist/server.js
npm run start:worker # separate process for queues
```

## Node.js runtime

- **SSOT:** `.nvmrc`, `package.json` `engines.node`, `@types/node` — all must match the same major (currently **24.x**).
- **Local:** `nvm use` (see `@docs/02-how-to/run-locally.md`).
- **Vercel:** Project Settings → Build and Deployment → Node.js Version → **24.x** (or rely on `engines.node` in `package.json`).
- **Worker host:** same Node major as API (long-lived `start:worker` process).

## Vercel

- Config: `@vercel.json` — SPA rewrites, `/api/*` → `api/index.ts`, robots/sitemap serverless routes. Public SEO pages `/`, `/catalog`, `/about`, `/contact`, `/privacy`, `/terms`, `/news`, `/news/:slug*`, `/account-tiers`, and `/p/*` route to `api/index` for SSR meta (see `routing.mdc` SEO section).
- Set all env vars in Vercel project settings (same names as `.env`).
- **Worker:** BullMQ worker is **not** a Vercel serverless function — run `start:worker` on a long-lived host (Railway, Fly, second Vercel service, etc.) with same `REDIS_URL` and `KV_REST_*`.
- **Worker-only install:** `npm ci --omit=dev` then `npm run start:worker` — UI packages (`preact`, `i18next`, etc.) live in `devDependencies` and are not needed at worker runtime. API/Vercel hosts must run `npm run build` (requires full `npm install` with devDependencies).
- **Worker-only install:** `npm ci --omit=dev` then `npm run start:worker` — UI packages (`preact`, `i18next`, etc.) live in `devDependencies` and are not needed at worker runtime. API/Vercel hosts must run `npm run build` (requires full `npm install` with devDependencies).

## Supabase

- **Migrations:** write and keep SQL in `supabase/migrations/` only (gitignored). See `@.cursor/rules/supabase.mdc`. Committed history: `@supabase/README.md`. Do not add new files under `docs/migrations/` or `docs/supabase-migrations/`.
- Edge functions / cron (e.g. token daily reset): see `docs/archive/SUPABASE_EDGE_FUNCTIONS.md` — verify against production before relying on archive steps.

## When changing deployment

- Update this rule and `@env.example.txt` together.
- Do not copy unverified steps from `docs/archive/DEPLOYMENT.md` or `VERCEL_DEPLOY_GUIDE.md` without checking the repo.
